i'm trying to  understand hyprctl. when i say hyprctl activewindow
i get Window 5538331bb490 -> myname@mycomputer:~:
etc
but then hyprctl dispatch togglefloating address:55e8331bb490 says window not found
The reason your command is failing is that hyprctl requires addresses to be prefixed with 0x to be recognized as hexadecimals. 
When you run hyprctl activewindow, it displays the raw hex address (e.g., 5538331bb490). However, the dispatch command interprets that raw number incorrectly unless you explicitly tell it it's a hex address. 
Correct Syntax
To toggle floating using an address, use this format: 
bash
hyprctl dispatch togglefloating address:0x5538331bb490
Use code with caution.

Pro-Tip: Automated Address Handling
If you are writing scripts, you can use the -j (JSON) flag with jq to automatically grab the correctly formatted address:
The Manual Way: Add 0x to whatever hyprctl activewindow gives you.
The Scripting Way: Use this command to get the address of the currently active window and toggle its floating state immediately:
bash
hyprctl dispatch togglefloating address:0x$(hyprctl activewindow -j | jq -r '.address')
Use code with caution.

Why "Window not found" happens:
Missing Prefix: Without 0x, Hyprland might try to parse the string as a decimal or a different window identifier (like a title or class).
Typo in Address: Ensure you are copying the full hex string. Note that in your example, you provided 5538331bb490 but then tried to call 55e8331bb490 (a subtle 'e' instead of '3'); using the 0x$(...) subshell method above eliminates this risk. 
These technical guides explain how to correctly format window addresses for "hyprctl" commands and how to automatically extract them for scripting:
